s reflexes controlled by millions of neurons. Written in a fun, easy-to-comprehend style and filled with illuminating analogies, Our Intelligent Bodies also brings readers up to date on cutting-edge research into the wonders of human physiology. It will give you a new appreciation for the smart decisions our bodies are making when our brains aren’t paying attention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aHuman physiology. 0aOrgans (Anatomy) 0aOrgans (Anatomy). 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aHealth, Medicine, boby, intelligent bodies, Science, Life Sciences, Human Anatomy, Physiology, fitness, Vision, Hearing, Cochlea, Proprioception, Balance, Acid Base, pH Regulation, Cardiovascular, Hemodynamics, Respiration, Kidneys, Body Water, Gut, Nutrient, Nutrient Flow, Gary F. Merrill, pulmonary system, oxygen levels, second brain, neurons, physiological structures.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069033040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081359855040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813598550423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813598550.jpg  a978-3-11-069033-0  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK